body_html:
@mrry I would just start by compiling fresh and saving the compiler log and grep through and fix all instances of warning: missing return statement at end of non-void function spotted by the compiler. I don't think there are too many of them. I might do such a pass one day at work when I am waiting for some results from the cluster.

(There are lots and lots of stupid compiler warnings that I would like to fix. If warnings are enabled and then just ignored, kittens dies, etc.)
